*review {arg1}

CRITICAL — the gate YAML must parse. Write every free-text field (status_reason, finding, fix_recommendation, notes, etc.) as a block scalar (e.g. `status_reason: |`) on its own indented lines, NOT as a quoted string. Free text here routinely contains backticks, colons, apostrophes and SQL/code snippets, and quoting them has repeatedly produced invalid YAML that silently breaks Hammoc's gate detection. Block scalars need no escaping. After writing the gate file, re-read it and confirm it loads as valid YAML (e.g. run a quick parse); if it fails, fix and rewrite before finishing.

When you write the quality gate, if the gate decision is CONCERNS or FAIL, also record it in the story so Hammoc tracks that a fix is pending. Append this exact line inside the story's QA Results section, replacing the placeholder with the gate's `updated:` value you just wrote:
<!-- hammoc:qa-fix gate="<paste the gate's updated value>" applied="false" -->
For a PASS or WAIVED gate, do not add this marker.